From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jami Daemon <jami@jami.net>
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2026 20:42:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] storage: guard against null storage bucket on expire

Storage::expire iterates over the stored values and, for every value
that has expired, forwards the removal to the StorageBucket that owns
its accounting through ValueStorage::store_bucket. That pointer can be
null for values that are not tracked by a persistence bucket (for
example locally produced values). Calling StorageBucket::erase() through
a null pointer dereferences the bucket members with a null "this",
producing a NULL_CLASS_PTR_READ (0xc0000005) crash inside
StorageBucket::erase, reached from Storage::expire / Dht::expireStore.

Only forward the erase to the bucket when the pointer is valid.
---
 include/opendht/storage.h | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/opendht/storage.h b/include/opendht/storage.h
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/include/opendht/storage.h
+++ b/include/opendht/storage.h
@@ -318,7 +318,8 @@ Storage::expire(const std::map<ValueType::Id, ValueType>& types, time_point now)
             break;
         if (not deleted.empty())
             total_size -= it->data->size();
-        it->store_bucket->erase(*it->data, *this);
+        if (it->store_bucket)
+            it->store_bucket->erase(*it->data, *this);
         deleted.emplace_back(std::move(it->data));
         it = values.erase(it);
     }
